Service Cloud SMS Terminology

To set up an SMS channel in Service Cloud, get familiar with terms like P2P, A2P, short codes, long codes, and segmentation.

Standard SMS channels are scheduled for retirement. Upgrade your standard SMS channels to enhanced channels before February 14, 2026, to avoid service interruptions.

Message Types

Person-to-Person (P2P)
Describes conventional two-way SMS or MMS messaging between individuals.
Application-to-Person (A2P)
Refers to anything that isn’t considered P2P, including chatbots and automated campaigns.

Message Use Case
Relevant when determining a solution for your company:
Inbound: Sent from a customer to your company’s number.
Outbound: Sent from your company’s number to a customer.
Automated Outbound: Bulk or outbound messages triggered by an action in Salesforce.
Number Types

Long Codes: Standard phone numbers like landlines, mobile numbers, and toll-free numbers.
A2P Long Code: A number used specifically for A2P communication.
Short Codes: Supported only in the US and Canada. Used for sending high-volume A2P messages.

Other Terms
SMS Messages: Sent over a cellular network, supporting text content.
MMS Messages: Sent over a cellular network, used to send pictures, video, audio, and phone contacts.
Segmentation: If an SMS message is more than 140 bytes, it's segmented into multiple messages.
title: SMS Terminology in Service Cloud
